/-- The first Fox-compatible profile reinterpreted through existing GIFT geometry.

The codebase already carries the two numbers required by the rank-one Fox
screen:

* `14 = dim(G2) = 2 * dim(K7) = 2 * |Fano lines|`;
* `11 = D_bulk`, and `b3 = dim(K7) * D_bulk`.

This is not yet a constructed discriminant link.  It is a concrete internal
geometric target: a Donaldson discriminant whose meridians are indexed by the
G2/Fano double-incidence geometry and whose fixed-block relation rank is the
M-theory bulk dimension.
-/
def giftInternalDonaldsonFoxProfile : DonaldsonRankOneFoxRelationProfile :=
  rankOneFoxRelationProfile GIFT.Core.dim_G2 GIFT.Core.D_bulk 0

